<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="page-header">
    <h1>About FitTrack</h1>
</section>

<section class="about-content">
    <p>
        FitTrack is a simple, personal workout logging application built with
        <strong>Node.js</strong>, <strong>Express</strong>, <strong>EJS</strong>
        and <strong>MySQL</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
        The goal of FitTrack is to help you stay consistent with your training
        by giving you a clean, easy-to-use log of all your workouts. You can
        record different types of exercise &mdash; from strength training with
        sets and reps to cardio sessions tracked by duration.
    </p>

    <h2>What you can do</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Register an account and log in securely</li>
        <li>Add, edit and delete your workout entries</li>
        <li>Search your log by exercise name or category</li>
        <li>View your full workout history in date order</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Built with</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Node.js &amp; Express &mdash; server and routing</li>
        <li>EJS &mdash; server-side HTML templating</li>
        <li>MySQL &mdash; relational database storage</li>
        <li>bcrypt &mdash; secure password hashing</li>
        <li>express-session &mdash; login session management</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
